The paper describes a machine learning approach to creating a simulator for predicting the next state of a patient with sepsis, based on historical patient records. This involves using a combination of techniques including a Variational Auto-Encoder, Mixture Density Network, and RNN. The paper also mentions the use of Deep Q-Learning for learning a policy for sepsis treatment. Based on these factors, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
